\begin_layout Problem
Assume a monochromatic plane wave strikes a thick slab of glass of an aquarium
 at normal incidence.
 Find the minimum and maximum transmission coefficients.
 The water has 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{1}=4/3$
\end_inset

, glass 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{2}=1.5$
\end_inset

, air 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{3}=1$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An incident beam goes from the water to the glass.
 The transmitted amplitude is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
E_{0T}=\Big(\frac{2n_{1}}{n_{1}+n_{2}}\Big)E_{0I}
\]

\end_inset

This transmitted wave then becomes an incident wave on the boundary between
 the glass and air.
 So the transmitted wave in the air is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
E_{0T}' & = & \Big(\frac{2n_{2}}{n_{2}+n_{3}}\Big)E_{0T}\\
 & = & \Big(\frac{2n_{2}}{n_{2}+n_{3}}\Big)\Big(\frac{2n_{1}}{n_{1}+n_{2}}\Big)E_{0I}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The transmission coefficient from water to air is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
T & = & \frac{\epsilon_{3}v_{3}}{\epsilon_{1}v_{1}}\Big(\frac{E_{0T}'}{E_{0I}}\Big)^{2}\\
 & = & \frac{n_{3}}{n_{1}}\Big(\frac{2n_{2}}{n_{2}+n_{3}}\Big)^{2}\Big(\frac{2n_{1}}{n_{1}+n_{2}}\Big)^{2}\\
 & = & \frac{16n_{3}n_{1}n_{2}^{2}}{(n_{2}+n_{3})^{2}(n_{1}+n_{2})^{2}}\\
 & = & \frac{16(1)(4/3)(1.5)^{2}}{(1.5+1)^{2}(4/3+1.5)^{2}}\\
 & = & 0.96
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

